headline: Why Target (TGT) Stock Is Down Today
summary: Shares of general merchandise retailer Target (NYSE:TGT) fell 4% in the afternoon session after the major indices continued to retreat (Nasdaq -1.5%, S&P 500 -1.2%) amid profit-taking and renewed concerns about tariffs. Investors reacted to a federal court ruling that most of President Trump's global tariffs were illegal, raising uncertainty over trade policy and the fiscal impact of potential refunds. headline: Clean Simple Eats Introduces Two New Target-Exclusive Clear Protein Water Flavors
summary: Clean Simple Eats (CSE), a leading brand in the health and wellness space, is introducing a beautiful new can design for its popular Clear Protein Water line, as well as two new delicious flavors: Blackberry Vanilla, which is juicy and rich, and Peach Mango Crème, which is smooth and peachy-sweet. The new flavors debuted at nearly 2,000 Target® stores and online at Target.com on Aug. 31.

headline: Kibble's New Best Friend: Stella & Chewy's Launches at Target
summary: Stella & Chewy's, the category leader in the freeze-dried raw pet food space, is excited to announce its national launch at Target, bringing its signature nutrition-boosting toppers and meals to one of the country's most beloved retailers.
